text:
last night i received a message that made me sick to my stomach — i was sent this on facebook messenger by someone who sexually assaulted me when i was 19—
.
.
someone i knew. someone i was dating. someone who pretended to think it was a big deal and apologize just to appease me at the time. . .and here is proof that this person is still a predator. proof that they feel smug that they ‘got away with it’ . . proof as a man, they feel safe and secure knowing how hard it is to prove he said she said scenarios. . proof that we can’t stay silent. . . not anymore
.
.
if only his girlfriend and two daughters knew the truth
.
.
💔💔💔
.
.
i will no longer be silent. not for your comfort. this is real. this is my life. this is my story
.
.

text:
i’m sick. but not just with a seasonal cold. my very being is sick at the current state of affairs in the u.s. 
i’ve written and deleted several times recently because i just can’t find the right words. i can’t make sense of what is going on. there are no words. there is no sense.
my heart hurts for those that are hurting. that are reliving trauma. i’m reliving it with you. 
my heart hurts that so many people have had their voice taken from them out of fear. my voice has been taken as well. 
my heart hurts that my fellow humans are being devalued. i feel that way as well. 
my heart hurts that this is the america and the culture that i’m raising my daughters in. 
but, i am proud and thankful for all of my fellow humans that are standing up. that are taking their voice, their power back. and, i stand beside you and behind you. i support you. i believe you. and i believe her.
this is our time to rise and stand and scream and shout for what is right. what is fair. and what should have been equal and just from the beginning. 
these are incredibly hard, emotional times that we are living in. in a time when every topic is so divisive and we are so emotionally invested (and exhausted) it is beyond important to be kind. to offer support. to listen. to care for one another. we are all humans- we have that in common. so, let’s care for our fellow humans as if our life depends on it, because it does. 
the second photo has phone numbers to call if you need support. and, i am always here as well. 
#ibelieveher #ibelieveyou #ihearyou #iseeyou #isupportyou #metoo

text:
not many people know this because i don't feel the need to share or perhaps because i have been fearful of having other's know that i too am a survivor...
dr. christine blasey ford is nothing less than a courageous woman that has gone up against an entire system to speak her truth. .
thank you for your bravery dr. balsey ford... you ma'am are a pillar of hope for women everywhere right now. .
.
brett kavanaugh like every other spineless sexual predator out there is a dirty liar that will say and do anything to protect his own ass. he has been seen as a "champ" for women's rights throughout the years... of course he would i'm sure it was a part of his scheme to redeem himself of a stained past. .
.
it's not the time for just believing survivors...but rather a time for actually caring and taking action. change is desperately needed not just for the sake of women but all of humanity.
remember where we all came from!!! #drblaseyford
#metoo #change #feminist #strength #survivor #courage #bravery #supremecourt #stopkavanaugh

text:
"there is never a good time to disclose sexual abuse. there is never a time that comes without severe consequences. someone’s reputation is always at stake. someone’s future is always at risk. we consistently focus on the consequences of the violator far more than the needs of the person who discloses [...] we surely see it is families, which is why many survivors have to go “no contact.” we see it in every single legal charge of a well-known person. unless a stranger drags a person into an alley and violently offends them, we will show little mercy and extend no comfort to the victim. less than 3% of rapist serve time for their crime. this is part of a large problem that intertwines lack of female body autonomy, male dominance, and privilege. we have to be sensitive to all of these issues in order to end rape among humans. we cannot choose to see only the aspect that serves us. big problems must be seen with big eyes and little egos. there will be more victims, and eventually, the accused will be someone you know and respect. we can’t choose morality by the degree of comfort if we want to change the world. if we are healing simply for the comfort of our own lives, rather than to change lives, then we are likely to become part of the problem. we are willing to risk being wrong 3% of the time to support the 97% of the truth-tellers." ― dr. rosenna bakari, #we2

text:
so much about what is happening in the news has so many women reliving their own personal traumas. one of many things that stunned me yesterday was dr. christine blasey ford’s seemingly throw away comment, “i am used to being collegial”. as a psychotherapist, and as a survivor of trauma, i see in myself and in survivor’s of physical, sexual and emotional trauma that i have worked with,  a reflexive impulse to be quiet, undemanding, hyperaware of the needs of others, overly solicitous, and extremely polite and kind—all as a kind of message to the world “don’t hurt me—i am not going to challenge you”. i often laugh at my reflexive impulse to apologize to a table if i bump into it, but it isn’t funny—it is a trauma reaction. that impulse comes out of a history where my being loud, assertive and free in my body came at enormous cost. .
as i reflect on how that impulse to be uber-polite, excessively collegial, more aware of others needs than i am my own, even after years of my own therapy and working as a therapist, i am more committed to taking up space, feeling whatever i feel without apology and no longer apologizing to that damn table. .
.
.

text:
an amputated 2018 #nobel season opens next week in #stockholm, without a #literature #prize for the first time in 70 years due to a #metoo scandal.

the medicine prize laureates will be revealed by the nobel assembly at the karolinska institute on monday, but many eyes will at the same time be turned to a stockholm courthouse for the verdict against a frenchman charged with rape who has close ties to the swedish academy.

the academy, which has awarded the prestigious literary distinction since the nobels were first awarded in 1901, has been torn apart by an acrimonious dispute over how to manage its affiliation with jean-claude arnault..#cgtn

text:
#heartwisdom
couldn't resist... i am a heretic. 🎨

the world is suffering a special diagnosis i learned in school. jfn... being a good student when i heard something i didnt know... i asked. 
it meant "just fucking nuts." i laughed. we have all these diagnosis in the "professional" world of psychology. we have laws in politics. we have rules with shame and guilt written all over them. jfn... and jesuit agenda. 
its a damn labrynth of double talk. confusion which propells emotions that feed the beast. stop. hold on to the sacred calm. our emotions are being triggered. 
now, i love triggers. they are the path to body temple wisdom. however, the triggers with this media shark frenzie is having its way with the collective unconscious. sure. women have been abused. i have been abused. #metoo

the three year witch hunt i endured in 1994 with "gibson, dunn, and krutcher" gutted me. [note: this was a church i sued for sexual discrimination and wrongful termination. i had had an affair with their cfo or was seduced by the cfo as i took the hit. they did nothing to him. the patriarchs had his back. i lost my career. the church had no mercy. it was brutal. i lived it. i was drug through the streets and survived. i found my sovereingty. i found heart wisdom.

its the same thing here. i feel it. it is about control of the culture. the times. there are lies. the system has been at this a long long time. it is all part and parcel of a larger whole. the woman is being used. look at the media. feel your own feeling. hell, are you kidding me... how long ago? he may or may not remember. alchohol was involved. the brain is an interesting thing on medications and drugs. i study this insane stuff... jfn.

self-regulation needed. fight or flight messes with our adrenals. 🙏🏻 in closing... respond. do not react. serves no one and the collective shadow has a field day. listen if you will, all i can say is energy vampires of our emotions are lurking... lol 🙃 its a game of the heart. holding sacred to mine. its my passion and truth. 
prayers of peace and strong body temples as we get through this next few months. be steady. be strong. we are heading for some transmutation of spirit. 🔥

text:
i believe you. i love you. i am sorry. cheers to all of the brave women who have stood up and told their stories to help shed light on a deeply sad issue that haunts women and girls all over our planet. to those women who choose not to share their traumas because it is too painful to relive. i pray for your peace and justice. the world is changing. slowly. i have hope. i have to. we have to. if you think this is a partisan issue and that democrats just want to use this to their political benefit it is not. this is a issue of right and wrong. please please please think about your daughters, mothers, sisters any woman in your life you love. love them. believe them when they tell you something has happened to them. 
#ibelieveher #ifyouareinnocentyouwouldtakethedamntest #metoo #womenempowerment #kavanaugh #keepcreepsoutofthesupremecourt

text:
most women i know are tired. tired of being dismissed, of us-and-them thinking, of drowning under the burden of proof that should be on those who’ve harmed. there is such deep-rooted duality in our society, but women speaking about their experiences is not the cause of it. it’s simply acknowledging what is already there. our very presence on a public platform is political. and, therefore, courageous. people coming forward with stories of trauma can never be measured by time — like dr ford, they will often only speak up if and when it may help others. and for those in power to foster a culture of silence, then criticise those for being silent, is just one hallmark of hypocrisy we need to recognise. spotlights are exposing these uncomfortable truths, and some may shield their eyes but that’ll only work for so long. 
most women i know are tired. tired of being silent. tired of being told to be silent, but to speak out, but to shut up, but to say something, but to pipe down, but to stop saying things that divide us, but to know their place as being less than. if you draw a line in the sand, and someone else points it out, who made it? can we please, please, please start working together? let’s open our ears instead of our mouths.
.
.
.
.
.
#drford #courage #riseup #werise #stillirise #metoo #metooquotes #sunrisequotes #brettkavanaugh #sunrise #newday #feminist #duality #feministquotes #ibelieveyou #spirituality #usandthem #higherconsciousness #menandwomen #philosophy #divinefeminine #equality #divineconsciousness #weworkbettertogether #soulful #divinemasculine #weareallone #humanity #unityconsciousness

text: so about a month ago, i started cutting back my rose bushes and flowers because they had not been properly taken care of and the entire plant so they were rotting and dying. it was hard work and this is just the beginning because now we are working on the back yard and the fruit trees. my bushes were basically bare, and now they are blooming beautifully! i like to think of this as baggage, and finally releasing, and the sense of peace it can bring us. opening up about my sexual assault yesterday has definitely opened up my heart for more growth. it will never be easy, but we find better ways to cope  and to help others. we work harder for change and show more empathy. #ibelieveher #ibelieveyou #metoo #sexualassault #rapevictim #sexualassaultawareneas #domesticviolence #standup #standtall #beheard

text:
in this video, the lead pastor, mr. steve gesualdi, of good news chapel in montreal @goodnewschapelmtl says: "when there is something false that takes place in this church, i will address it. and if people want to push me to the edge, i will address you and i will remove you myself because i am a shepherd of the flock of christ for this church"
.
first of all, there should never be a "when" for false teachings or false preachers to enter a church. secondly, if people are questioning you about something false they saw or heard, they are not pushing you to the edge, they just want to be informed. thirdly, if someone questioning you pushes you to the edge, then is it really safe for anyone to be under your care as a shepherd because if they ever question you, you'll lose your temper on them. this does not sound like a healthy church environment.
.
the pastor says that not only will he be pushed over the edge, but he will personally kick that person out of his church for doing what the bible encourages them to do in acts 17:11, which is to examine the scriptures to test if the things that we see or hear are true or not. this pastor is threatening to kick you out and excommunicate you if ever you ask him questions about something that seems false. he does not want to be questioned or challenged. this is a dangerous form of authoritarian leadership. we were blocked by the church's instagram account for asking questions.
.
.
youtube video title: "my way… or the highway (a preacher turned judge, jury and executioner)"
https://m.youtube.com/watch?v=ndpkzwexgxs&t=141s
.

text: president donald trump agrees to fbi investigation on sexual abuse allegations from christine blasey ford toward supreme court nominee brett kavanaugh. as a result the senate has agreed to push back the vote for a week to give time for the investigation. without the investigation it was almost a guarantee that kavanaugh would not be voted into the supreme court.  the senate pushed president trump between a rock and hard place giving him the option of the f.b.i. investigation or the likelihood that kavanaugh would not be voted into the supreme court. so hopefully, we, the american people get more knowledge out of this investigation but stay tuned i will keep everyone updated with information as i receive it.

text: faith is taking the first step even when you can not see the whole staircase.  faith is believing in yourself.  faith is trusting in magic.  faith is not confirming belligerent frat boy attempted rapists to the highest court in the land.  faith is not silencing women in favor of the status quo or to legislate a woman’s body without her permission.  faith is not patriarchy.  it is not hate.  it is not holding on to power in a death rattle because of fear of women or people of color.  i believe her.  why?  because i am her. because i have fought my way out of the back seat of a frat boys car and god’ damn it, it’s not “horseplay” or “boys will be boys,” it is called sexual assault.  if your reason for supporting brett cavanagh is faith, please reevaluate your relationship to god. #ibelieveher #ibelievechristineblaseyford #metoo #stopkavanaugh #smashthepatriarchy #heslying

text:
i will never forget the smell of his cologne, the orange and yellow geranimals outfit with the broken belt buckle from where he tried to grab me. i will always remember the weight of the dictionary or encyclopedia in my hand that i threw at him. i don’t remember his face, the color of his hair or the sound of his voice. i don’t remember his name or the apartment or my bedroom. i don’t remember a lot of things about that day but there are somethings that will stay with me forever. i was 7. 
today i wear black in solidarity with fellow victims of sexual violence. i wear black so that one day all of us can come out of the shadows and share our stories. i wear black to say #timesup. i wear black to let those in power know that we are here, we are pissed off, we never forget and we will no longer remain silent. i wear black to say #ibelieveher. i wear black to say #enoughisenough. 
later in october i have the privilege of being a featured storyteller along with @xoxy_alicia and @theplayprof at @bossbabesatx meetup on the 25th. we will be talking about how to be authentic and unabashedly ourselves. i planned on honoring this event by setting a challenge to take a daily selfie that reflects me wherever i am and however i feel, authentically. it is appropriate that this day of trauma, solidarity, and remembrance will be my first selfie of my challenge. i have struggled with taking selfies in the past and i want to change that (i have no idea what to do with my face 😱🤷🏻‍♀️🤔😳). #authenticliving #iammytestimony #authenticity #unabashedlyme #metoo #itsoktobeangry #whyiwearblack #consentissexy #couragethroughvulnerability

text:
i know first hand what it's like to be objectified. to know that that person is still out there and has not been brought to justice. it's a shitty feeling not being able to do anything about it. thank you doctor ford for standing up and telling your story. i'm happy to see something is finally being done, i'm happy that women are standing up and speaking the truth, and if it scares you because you have something to hide- good. those people deserve what's coming to them, because we deserve to feel safe no matter how much shoulder we might show. now, i'd rather have my instagram feed be filled with facials and pictures of my dog, but while i'd love to ignore politics and post about what i ate today, i just can't. sorry if it's not your view, but it's mine. i can't forget this issue, because in my experience it won't go away until you make it. thank you for your time.

text:
to all folks out there who are also victims of sexual assault, these last couple of days have been especially hard, and please make sure to be gentle with yourself. i see you and i hear you and i believe you. i’ve been feeling stuck in between breaths, like the air was sucker punched out of me. ••• because here’s the truth of it - they believe her. they just don’t care. ••• somehow that cuts even deeper. so know that you are loved, and cared about, and seen, tend to your precious and miraculous heart, and all together we will root down, stand tall, and breathe fire. .
.
to any men who wonder how they can better support womxn they love who have been victims of sexual assault (most of the womxn i know have) - now is a great time to check in and see how the person you love is feeling. listening is one of the most loving acts we can offer each other. .
.
.
#believe #metoo #riseup #wecanheal #wereallinthistogether #ibelieveher #iloveyou #believesurvivors

text:
there are many reasons as to why we don't share our stories and that is ok. 
no one should ever force you to share something that you are not ready to share, but i want you ladies to know that the longer we hold it in, the more damage we cause ourselves.

you don't have to share your story with just anyone. find someone you trust or even better seek professional help. there is nothing wrong with going to someone that actually went to school to help us out! and that way you won't have to worry about telling the wrong person either.

trust me, you are not alone. believe me when i say that it is not easy and it might never be easy, but you need to take care of yourself both mentally and physically. .
.
.
.

.
.
#empoweredselfdefense #isurvivor #metoo #believesurvivors #iamasurvivor

text:
the thought of posting this makes me feel sick to my stomach, which i feel is all the more reason to post it. with all the sexual assulalt news going on, i've sat silently but reflected a lot on my own experience. i figure it's finally time i talk about it, with a ridiculously hilarious and embarrassing picture for comic relief.

in high school i so desperately wanted to be liked. i wanted to fit it, but i was different. i wasn't popular, i was never sought after, and i really didn't have many friends (other than my sister--thanks for letting me share this picture of you too). i was entering my senior year of high school and still had never been kissed.

a guy i knew asked me to go on a date before he left for college, at west point. he knew i had never been kissed. he knew who i was and he knew my innocence. i believe he purposefully took advantage of me. i know he knew i didn't like it as he apologized after and then drove me home. i didn't even know what he had done. i didn't even know it was a thing. i was very naive. i just knew i didn't like it. i knew i wanted it to stop, but i didn't know how to speak up. that's where so much of the shame comes in.

i should have said something. i didn't say no. it technically was "for me." and on top of it, i know so much worse has been done to so many so i feel like my story isn't enough as silly as that sounds.

but, my silence is still hurting me and others. i didn't say no, but that doesn't mean what happened was okay. it doesn't mean that it's my fault or that i was wrong. i just felt like i needed to say something for those who don't have a voice. your voice matters, your story matters, you did nothing wrong, and you aren't alone.

#metoo #metoomovement #yourvoicematters #flashbackfriday

text:
today i feel angry. i feel triggered. i feel like i have been hit by a tidal wave and dragged out to sea.

i am sitting with my anger. not acting out in it, not repressing it. i am allowing myself to feel it fully. i feel it in the tightness in my shoulders, in the clenching of my jaw. i feel it pulse in my fists. i feel my heart rate kick up and i notice i keep holding my breath. 
i have been watching the hearing unfold, reliving my own experiences of multiple sexual assaults. i remember that none of the 3 men who molested or raped me have served time. i remember that these offenses occurred when i was 3, 12, and 19. i am so angry on behalf of every young girl who has had something taken from her that could never be returned. i am angry for every womxn who has been violated. i am angry for our collective lost sense of safety.

sitting in this anger with full awareness i know that my anger is not without reason. my anger is a divine catalyst for change.

the time has come to focus that energy and direct it towards building a new way of being. this anger is centered in love. it is centered in the belief that we have a right to be safe in our bodies and free of forced sex.

i will not stop speaking up. i will not stop teaching trauma survivors meditation. i will not stop being loud and angry about this until policies that govern the bodies of womxn change. i will not stop being loud and angry until we repair this culture of rape, until we stop blaming victims and start holding sexual abusers accountable. 
anger has a purpose and a place. it is the fuel we put on the inner fire which burns away all mental impurities, until there is nothing left but clarity. 
i offer my anger to kali. may she take this pain, this anger, and transform it into radical love. 
jai maa!

#kali #kalima #mahakali #anger #sexualassault #rapesurvivor #sexualassaultsurvivor #brettkavanaugh #christineblaseyford #womensrights #metoo #silentnomore #divinefeminine #believesurvivors

i will not stop speaking up. i will not stop teaching trauma survivors meditation. i will not stop being loud and angry about this until policies that govern the bodies of womxn change. i will not stop being loud and angry until we repair this culture of rape, until we stop blaming victims and sta holding sexual abusers accountable. 
anger has a purpose and a place. it is the fuel we put on the inner fire which burns away all mental impurities, until there is nothing left but clarity. 
i offer my anger to kali. may she take this pain, this anger, and transform it into radical love. 
jai maa!

text:
feeling the collective sorrow, outrage, frustration, indignation, exhaustion that all survivors and allies are working through today.

i know the patriarchy is closer to falling than its ever been but it’s still a dangerous beast that continues to breathe fire onto our wounds.

i take heart in the fact that so many of us are gathering our power and raising our voices louder than ever before! for every abominable situation like kavanaughs approval, more people’s eyes are opened to the disturbing distortion of the priorities and values of the ruling elite. 
the fact remains that we have existed in a manufactured patriarchy where males are prized and females are devalued for at least the last two millennia. this was intentionally created and a grand plan was implemented to systematically separate women from our power. one of the main tools for this was specifically using sexual violence to shame and disempower females. their weapon continues as evidenced by this sickness that still makes so many of us suffer and is deemed “no big deal” by those in power. even though it may not feel like it today the tide is turning and the feminine is rising. 
check on each other today, take care of yourself this wknd, reach out and share your process, it’s a heavy time.

text:
sob uma crescente pressão nas fileiras republicanas, donald trump ordenou nesta sexta-feira (28) uma investigação do fbi sobre o seu indicado à suprema corte dos estados unidos, acusado de agressão sexual, atrasando uma aguardada votação do senado sobre a confirmação do juiz brett kavanaugh.
o juiz conservador aceitou cooperar com a investigação, em uma semana na qual a sua indicação à mais alta instância jurídica americana esteve rodeada de uma intensa polêmica.
os democratas pediram a investigação do fbi sobre as acusações de christine blasey ford, de 51 anos, que diz que kavanaugh tentou estuprá-la quando os dois eram estudantes em 1982.
seu depoimento aos senadores comoveu grande parte dos americanos na quitna-feira, enquanto outros tomaram partido do juiz, em um país profundamente polarizado. brett kavanaugh negou categoricamente todas as acusações.
as investigações serão “limitadas a acusações plausíveis” apresentadas contra o juiz conservador, anunciou o comitê judicial do senado.
finalmente, um senador republicano foi fundamental para o voto – jeff flake -, que conseguiu forçar a abertura de uma investigação.

text:
today was a day where i got sucked in- to the news and the drama and the reality that we as women face. regardless of who is right or wrong, regardless of what political slant you are on. this isn’t about a political party stance, but about respecting humanity. we alone are in control of our reactions. we can attack, hate, judge and ridicule. or we can seek to understand. i’m thrilled that the hype didn’t force a decision and that we can take a deep breath and do what should have happened in the first place - a real investigation. this is not about digging up and throwing the past in people’s faces. this is about how we interact with one another now. it’s about the responses coming out now and the division in our country now, and the response kavanaugh could have made to help me understand his ability to be a bipartisan judge who weighs all aspects of an accusation. 
my husband is a man. he is masculinity and femininity. we all carry both. he is so much the epitome of my dream man, and i knew him in our wild and crazy years. and no amount of alcohol ever, ever, even sent his mind down the path of disrespecting women. 
he has pushed me more than any other to do things on my own and to be an independent woman, because he never has viewed women as a lesser being or incapable of anything. reacting with accusations and yelling and pointing fingers is something that tears apart homes and families, yet we accept this as okay when it comes to running the largest home of all...our homeland. 
please. stand up in love. stand up for what you believe in, you don’t have to remain silent. speak truthfully, and own it. no one can take away your truth and your feelings. those are yours. and everyone deserves respect. you have to give space for it, and the opportunity to listen. 
thanks to @magamamas for putting it succinctly and @katenorthrup for resharing. and thanks to the many who are speaking up and sharing their stories, finding healing and support, and navigating through this all as everywhere we look is another trigger to trauma so many women face. this affects every single one of us. #metoo #kavanaughhearings #womensrightsarehumanrights #weallneedtobeheard #namaste

text:
kavanaugh. this is my first time as a witness of a demonstration in the usa. my photographer's instinct was stronger and it threw me into the street early in the morning to look and see. i know that this is a unique and interesting moment in the history of this country and, paraphrasing pablo de la torriente brau, my eyes are made to see and my camera to tell the things i see. i believe too.

kavanaugh. esta es mi primera vez como testigo de una manifestación en usa. mi instinto de fotógrafo pudo más y me lanzó a la calle bien temprano a buscar y ver. sé que este es un momento único e interesante en la historia de este país y, parafraseando a pablo de la torriente brau, mis ojos están hechos para ver y mi cámara para contar las cosas que veo. yo también creo.

kavanaugh. this is my first time as a witness of a demonstration in the usa. my photographer's instinct was stronger and it threw me into the street early in the morning to look and see. i know that this is a unique and interesting moment in the history of this country and, paraphrasing pablo de la torriente brau, my eyes are made to see and my camera to tell the things i see. i believe too.

kavanaugh. esta es mi primera vez como testigo de una manifestación en usa. mi instinto de fotógrafo pudo más y me lanzó a la calle bien temprano a buscar y ver. sé que este es un momento único e interesante en la historia de este país y, parafraseando a pablo de la torriente brau, mis ojos están hechos para ver y mi cámara para contar las cosas que veo. yo también creo.

text: for every person out there that is a survivor of sexual assault, i believe you. i believe you even if you’ve never shared your story out loud. i believe you if you have no evidence. i believe you even if an eye witness won’t testify on your behalf. i believe you regardless of the countless reasons people come up with to brush off the severity of what happened. i believe you. 💙if someone is being brave enough to share what has happened to them, please don’t discount it because of when it happened or they have no “proof” most times, there is zero proof. many victims of sexual assault, harassment, or domestic violence hide their stories from everyone around them. be kind, be patient, and be supportive if someone reaches out to share their story. #ibelieveyou #metoo #takebackthenight #whyididntreport #cancelkavanaugh #nomeansno #survivor #awareness #ibelievedrford #webelieveyou 💙 #standwithwomen #ibelieveher #believesurvivors #believewomen

text:
to all the women who feel disempowered right now:
i’m so sorry you’re feeling how you do. i am with you. i am here for a cry, a conversation, an escape. there is nothing i can do that will ever make anything better for you. i wrote a book to try though. i hope you know it’s my love letter to every single one of you.
to the men who are feeling triggered:
i’m so sorry for your pain. i’m so sorry you know mine. i’m so sorry you may have a harder time getting people to believe you than me. im here for you.
for the men and women who believe survivors and don’t know our pain:
thank you for believing in something that you did not experience yourself. your belief is some kind of magic.
to the men and women who don’t believe:
i hope you never have to go through the trauma we did to believe. i hope that the people in your life who have been assaulted have a forgiveness streak a mile wide. i hope so many things for you.
.
i hope one day, we don’t have to debate this, and that it will seem absurd we drug our own trauma out for weeks, and put a woman on trial for a man’s job interview.
#believesurvivors #wearearcadia
.
.
.
.
.

text:
i've seen women share their stories, so i'll share mine. 
at 15 i was raped by my boyfriend. i did not know that our relationship was toxic until it happened. we walked in the woods near our highschool and he forced himself on me. all i remember is saying "what are you doing?!" repetitivaly..and eventually going numb. i was a virgin.  i never told anyone out of shame, i didn't tell my therapist and even my own mother. he was manipulative and emotionally abusive, i was afraid of him. 
he threatened to tell my friends and dirty my name if i told anyone, and i believed him. in front of our friends i seemed fine, i didn't think anyone would believe me if i fessed up. i was scared of being dismissed, called a liar, or abandoned by the people i trusted. who would believe the girl with a therapist? 
when my family left germany, he told all my friends. he turned my best friend against me, and that isolation lead me to attempting to take my life for a 2nd time. 
i finally told my mom the story when i was 21. i broke her heart for keeping my silence for so long. you ask yourself why women won't come forward right away and this one reason why. those fears never go away, and rapists like  brock turner get away with it because of disbelief towards the victims of these crimes. 
#whyididntreportit #metoo

text:
"i am not here today because i want to be. i am terrified. i am here because it is my civic duty to tell you what happened to me."
(from the opening statement of dr fords testimony)

here is a photo from the teaching today when i showed up to give my talk with a full heart. i am in la teaching buddhism at #communeretreat. meanwhile hearing the news and having all these conversations about sexism, assault, and misogyny... to all the people out there sharing your stories of sexual assualt, i believe you. thank you for your courage to speak up in the face of trauma, abuse, harassment, ivasions of privacy, stress and stigma. 🙏🏽#ibelieveyou  on days like these, when i feel like being very quiet and speaking out *at the same time* i find peace in reciting the 21 taras prayer. it calls forth the energy of the fierce love, action, intensity and power of the female bodhisattva tara... "homage, tara, quick one,
heroine whose eyes flash like lightening,
born from the opening corolla of the lotus face
of the lord of the triple world.

homage, mother whose face is filled
with the light of an array of a hundred full autumn moons,
shining with the brilliant open light
of the hosts of a thousand stars.

homage, ture, terrible lady,
who annihilates the warriors of delusion,
slaying all enemies with a frown
of wrath on her lotus face.

homage, mother, her hand adorns her heart
in a mudra that symbolizes the three jewels.
adorned with the universal wheel,
she radiates turbulent light.

homage, mother, who hits the earth
with the palm of her hand,
who pounds on it with her feet.
frowning wrathfully, she shatters
the seven underworlds by the sound of hum.

homage, mother, blissful, virtuous, calm,
whose field of activity is peaceful nirvana,
endowed with the true perfection of sv aha and om, conquering great evils.

homage, mother, served by the ruler of the hosts of gods, by gods and kimnaras,
dispelling conflicts and bad dreams
with her armor of joy and splendor...." #ibelieveyou #ibelievesurvivors #ibelievewomen #timesup #metoo #rapeculture #istillbelieveanitahill #unstuck #listentowomen #buddhistwomen #pemakhandro #bebrave #believesurvivors #sexismhurtseveryone #womenempowerment

text:
the fall of 1993 i was 16, dating at boy at i.u and i drove a group of friends down to go to a frat party at my boyfriends fraternity. we were staying with a girlfriend that was a freshman and living in a dorm down there.
.
the why store was playing at the party. i drank a little beer but not much bc i never really liked beer and i was nervous and out of place.
.
we went back to my friends dorm. she had a couple older male friends there visiting from her hometown. she left to get pizza from mellow mushroom and left me there... bc they didn’t have room for all of us. .
one of the male friends came back. he came on to me and i pushed him away. he forced himself onto me and raped me. i fled to the dorm bathroom and shook in a bathroom stall and that’s where my friends found me. my friend that lived there didn’t want to believe me bc that was her friend but my highschool friends that came with me sat and held me and cried with me. we left in the middle of the night and drove home. i didn’t tell my parents bc i thought they’d be mad i wasn’t where i said i’d be and i drank some beer.
.
i was a virgin.
.
this wasn’t the first or last time i dealt with unwanted advances from men. .
i told my friends mom bc she was like a second mom. i told my husband and counselors along the way. my relationships have been hard and trust isn’t easy with me.
.
i’m one of millions ... my story isn’t unique but i know for me when i watch dr. fords testimony i know it could of been me up there. 25 years ago this happened. but i still remember the eagles cd was playing i can’t listen to that to this day, i remember his clothes, cologne and many little things. i to didn’t report it bc i was afraid. it’s not unusual for us to keep these intimate details bc we fear for exactly what’s happening right now. .
so when i know ppl in my life that support kavanaugh or at least support not looking into the allegations i guess it makes me feel a bit like they wouldn’t believe me either.
.
for many of us this brings up a lot. and i applaud the men that stand up for us and the warrior women fighting as we will keep doing for little , warrior girls like daphne!
.
#metoo #christineblaseyford
name: Thrifting Wanderluster

text:
💪stronger together💪
our world has disappointed me the last few years (mainly because i started paying attention to the world around me more recently than i care to admit) - i personally never liked politics, in fact i hated it so much in high school i would leave the common area if it was being discussed - it left me with a horrible feeling of everyone yelling but never being heard, the opposing side not being open minded, and ultimately nothing was accomplished 💪 as i’ve matured into a young women living in modern america, i have seen first hand why & how important it is to stand up for your rights, your beliefs, and every human (women, child & man) around you - because the sad truth is not many politicians will do that for you 💪 this isn’t a political post, but just a reminder to be respectful, aware, listen, and try to put yourself in someone else’s shoes in order to see a different perspective on a situation 💪 i, along with countless women & men in the world, have experienced unwanted advances, comments, and feared for what would happen - i was naive enough to think my voice wouldn’t make a difference but a close friend reminded me that i have this platform to share, inspire, create, motivate & encourage all of you to stand together and stand up for what you deserve - and you deserve only the best 💪 #metoo #strongertogether #girlssupportinggirls #landofpleasanteating

text:
imagine you’ve been sexually assaulted.
imagine you have to relive every horrendous, traumatic detail of your ordeal in front of millions of people, on live television.
imagine one of the most powerful men in the world taking to social media to question your honesty & integrity.
then imagine having to watch as the aforementioned powerful man not only publicly defends your attacker, but recommends him for life-long service in a role that would see him decide what is just, fair & lawful.
this is why women don’t report sexual assault. because they fear they won’t be believed. because they worry they might even be blamed. because they think people might accuse them of making it up, or remembering it wrong. because they worry that they might be belittled, patronised, told they’ve simply misunderstood. that they’ll be shamed. that they’ll be interrogated. that they might have to go over & over every painful detail, only to watch their attacker walk free. 
dr christine blasey ford may not get the justice she deserves. but a thousand salutes to her for standing up for herself & for all women by having the courage to speak out, especially against someone in such a position of power & privilege. to quote an article i read a while back in @thepooluk : “if only we as a society were as horrified at the idea of a woman being sexually assaulted, as we are at the idea of a man being wrongly accused”. #metoo #whyididntreport #stopkavanaugh #drford #christineblaseyford #brettkavanaugh #endsexualviolence #believesurvivors #smashthepatriarchy #justice #feminism #womensrights #womensupportingwomen #girlpower #thisisamerica #ruthdrawsthings
name: Ruth Mary Annie

then imagine having to watch as the aforementioned powerful man not only publicly defends your attacker, but recommends him for life-long service in a role that would see him decide what is just, fair & lawful.
this is why women don’t report sexual assault. because they fear they won’t be believed. because they worry they might even be blamed. because they think people might accuse them of making it up, or remembering it wrong. because they worry that they might be belittled, patronised, told they’ve simply misunderstood. that they’ll be shamed. that they’ll be interrogated. that they might have to go over & over every painful detail, only to watch their attacker walk free. 
dr christine blasey ford may not get the justice she deserves. but a thousand salutes to her for standing up for herself & for all women by having the courage to speak out, especially against someone in such a position of power & privilege. to quote an article i read a while back in @thepooluk : “if only we as a society were as horrified at the idea of a woman being sexually assaulted, as we are at the idea of a man being wrongly accused”. #metoo #whyididntreport #stopkavanaugh #drford #christineblaseyford #brettkavanaugh #endsexualviolence #believesurvivors #smashthepatriarchy #justice #feminism #womensrights #womensupportingwomen #girlpower #thisisamerica #ruthdrawsthings

text:
i believe survivors. of course i do. is there really any other sustainable option? this culture of denial needs to meet its end—and all those who uphold it need to do their part in that (that includes me & you by the way). - 
to any survivors, i am here to support you in any way that i can. it’s okay to take time off social media, to need some extra care, to lean on your community. there is no such thing as “not that bad” for things that never should have happened in the first place. your experiences are real and your feelings are valid. there space for your anger and truth, for your validation and healing—whatever that looks like for you in this moment. - 
to the allies. we’ve got some work to do. reach out to your people, check in on them, remind them that you believe and love them. post & share thoughtfully. look at the bias that you have, find ways to address them. don’t rely on already marginalized people to do that work for you for free. find ways to use your privilege and resources to centralize the voices of people that don’t have the same access. listen more than you speak.
- 
to everyone else. if you’re not actively working to change it, you are complacent in its existence. think about why you are okay with that. take a look at how this culture benefits you. ask the women and trans people in your life what measures they take to protect themselves in their day. listen. ask the cis men in your life that same question. notice the differences. question if you are really okay with living in a world like that. don’t settle for a yes.

text:
just because she isn't saying no...
does not mean she is saying yes.
drunk or drugged and unable to make proper decisions means no.
silence means no.
wait...means no.
no thanks means no.
uhh...means no.
staying still means no.
consent is voluntary, sober, enthusiastic, verbal, non-coerced, continual, active, honest.
lack of consent=rape/sexual assault
sexual assault is not just a "women's issue", it's a community problem.
ending sexual and gender-based violence is everyone's responsibility.
victim blaming needs to stop!
i feel that voicing this is just one small step into spreading awareness and information on this issue.
i stayed silent for far too long on this.
as someone who's been through a few traumatic situations when i was younger, i just want to tell the ones who are living through painful memories, guilt, and shame...
it is not your fault.
it is absolutely not your fault no matter what your mind tells you, or what anyone tells you.
i know exactly what it's like to blame yourself and feel so guilty and traumatized that there's days where you want to somehow crawl away from your own skin.
i know exactly what it's like to have a hard time trusting anyone after your trust was crushed by someone you thought you knew.
i know exactly what it's like to feel that it's your fault and that you deserved it, or to doubt anything happened.
i know exactly what it's like to be afraid of telling anyone because of the fear of backlash, or them not believing you.
"you wake up every morning to fight the same demons that left you so tired the night before, and that, is bravery."
we believe you. ❤
you are not alone. ❤
you are strong and loved.
"here's to strong women.
may we know them.
may we be them.
may we raise them."
and here's to spreading awareness on the topic that should be fkn common sense but isn't.
anything other than a continual yes, means no.
here's to being a voice for the women who are quietly pushing through their traumatic experiences. you're not alone. we believe you. you are strong.
love you! ❤
ps: go follow @ohilyssa and her hubz @sir_elsea
thank you for being the voice for so many and spreading awareness.
__________

text:
amid all the #metoo, my son (age 10) came home in tears, because his experience of 4th grade is that the girls are making all the rules, and getting all the jobs they volunteer for. he is feeling that the boys are being left out. 
i am trying to make sense of it. he doesn't want me to approach his teacher, who i guess dismissed his comment about the situation as "stereotyping." this is not a comment on his teacher, as i also recognize that when speaking with a 10yo boy, there is a lot of context that is simply not communicated, because he probably does not yet know how. but my son is incredibly observant, and i can say quite sensitive and insightful. 
is this a developmental stage and behavior? and why does it feel to him that the girls are in a place of power? and maybe that is how it should be or needs to be for our place and time along the continuum of cultural change? 
as a mother, i feel that my role is to support him in his frustration, and to let him know that his voice is valid and valuable, and if and when he feels it needs to be heard, with compassion to all beings involved, he will speak his own truth.

sons. and mothers. and daughters. may we all be free from this suffering. <3

text:
the weight of sexual assault
.
5 weeks ago i decided to go back into therapy to deal with a childhood rape that happened when i was 10. i was empowered by the #metoo movement and summoned the courage. i’ve done lots of therapy throughout my life, mostly analysis and talk therapy. i became a dance therapist but avoided any clients with trauma. instead i niched in autism. 
the therapy i’m doing now is specifically for trauma, especially complex trauma like mine, trauma that continued for years after the originating event. it’s called crm (comprehensive resource model), a powerful and safe way to re-experience trauma and break the loop of dissociation and shame that accompanies the memories without being re-traumatized. 
crm integrates emdr, psychotherapy, somatic experiencing, deep and conscious breathing techniques and shamanic and spiritual practices including finding your animal spirit to guide you and keep you safe. mine is a bat. a winged mammal. that was a surprise. bats are the protector of the night and the dark. nurturing and family oriented. the message from my bat was “you were born to soar and i am here to guide you and keep you safe.” i am blown away by the process and the progress i have made in 5 short weeks. “coming out” about this trauma is crazy liberating! i told no one at the time and when i started hearing other boys say things to me like “how’s carl...?” it was clear he had boasted to his friends. i denied it! it wasn’t sex! i didn’t ask for that, it was rape! i didn’t know what sex was or rape at 10 years old. it was 1971. i remember asking a friend who was a year older “can i get pregnant if i haven’t gotten my period yet?” it all began the day i walked in on my brother and his friends smoking pot when i was 10. i guess my brother felt he had to ‘get’ something on me before i told mom and dad. so, he conspired with a friend that lived down the block to do the deed while my brother watched in the closet. i don’t remember the day of the week, or the month. but i can tell you the details of the room and the emotions i experienced. i just know it was summer because i was on my way to the pool, wearing my red and white one-piece swim suit,

10. you’re an optimist…

some say you’re too trusting or even naive. but your optimism is a gift. you approach the world with a child-like curiosity, and you always manage to see the good in people. your optimism makes you resilient in the face of hardship, and the people in your life are refreshed by your positivity.

11. …who’s prone to melancholy moods

you know the world isn’t perfect. things often fall short of your ideals, and meaning and inspiration can be hard to find. similarly, you crave deep, authentic connections with others, but these are usually few and far between. although adept at looking on the bright side, paradoxically, you may at times struggle with sad or depressed thoughts.

sometimes, these melancholy moods have more pragmatic roots. the downside of not pursuing traditional achievements is that it’s easy to feel like you’re losing out. if you’re getting underpaid or underappreciated, it’s especially easy to fall into cynicism. the infps who grow out of this are often the ones who chose to do at least a little planning around their earnings and career — because they start to feel less taken for granted. the external success is not important on its own, but it helps protect their inner happiness.

text_retweet:
don’t be pissed about the chaos in the white house, our government, our entertainment industry and more. i carry zero comment about who’s wrong or who’s right. you see, i’m grateful the “cage we were in”, was shook to its core, for if it wasn’t for all of that, i don’t think our voices would have been heard. there has been a rude “awakening” that calls for “healing”. finally, we have the opportunity to feel safe to discuss the pain we all have endured in emotional, physical and mental abuse. now, you can truly feel, that you’re not the only one that has to go through the healing process alone. now, those abusers, who come from poor programming of the past, can move onto and into a better programming that teaches them equality, educated them on proper  conduct in the home and workplace. as much as this hurts for all of us, and yes, i have been a victim of abuse in the home and workplace(s) too, i feel we are finally able to join together in this pain and grow together in the healing. this goes for men who have experienced vulnerable experiences too. let’s not separate or divide, let’s use this energy to teach, to heal, to forgive. holding onto the poison of anger will never give your abuser a lesson. you healing from it, so you can break free of this emotional prison will. speak up, inbox me if you need, i will listen and extend my heart to everyone, men and women who have dealt with abuse. just know you’re not the only one, i’m healing too. we can’t change the past, but, together, we can change the future. ❤️
•••••••••••••••••••••••••
#pleaserepost #pleaseshare #wetoo #metoo #onelove #givelove #heal

text:
in times now, where we are reliving our traumas and seeing stories from hundreds of thousand others, we need to remember to hold space. .

hold space for our own healing. hold space for openness. hold space for processing. hold space for stillness. hold space for connection. hold space for us to honor our own needs. hold space for our loved ones. hold space for conversations. hold space for others to feel safe. hold space for us to be able to go into the world the way we feel called to do us. .

but mostly, hold space for love.

brett kavanaugh is the symptom. rape culture and patriarchy is the disease. same with trump. same with the rapists outted by the #metoo movement (not to mention white supremacy, capitalism, etc). men, if you actually care...listen to women, and the women on the front lines of the anti-sexist, anti-rape culture, feminist movement and get to work. and if you’re a man, wondering if i’m talking about you, i can assure you that i am. you need to be a man that other men know stands against rape culture. that other men know won’t let this shit slide. that other men can come to you with their questions about what to do to be a part of the solution. we all have circles of influence, and we need to influence them. we don’t deserve credit for not being a kavanaugh, a trump, or a weinstein. the only way to change this world to make it safer for women and girls is to be preemptive and do the shit that you see almost no other men doing. when you see lots of women in your life re-posting an article or a meme about rape culture, but not men doing it, you do it. violence against women is *men’s* violence against women over 99% of the time. this is our job to fix. guys, next time you hear liberal men complaining about kavanaugh, ask “what are you doing to end rape culture?”

text_retweet:
#repost @annaabramzonart ・・・
this lady is my hero this week. and painting her was my therapy. thank you, dr. ford, for your bravery. our nation owes you a huge thank you. 
usually i paint my portraits over something that my subject has written — but i did not want to paint dr. ford over her statement of the horror of her attack. instead, i painted it over @senkamalaharris statement to her. “and so i want to thank you. i want to thank you for your courage and i want to tell you i believe you. i believe you.” shabbat shalom, friends. 
#metoo #ibelieveher #believesurvivors #feminist #stopkavanaugh #christineblaseyford #hero

man the planet energy is heavy. massive shift going on. and such a needed shift. meditating. yoga. sage. candles. self care like mad. out with the truth, in with the healing. 💜

text:
something bad happened to me years ago and i was debating on making a post about it. i have done #metoo posts but i'm trying to distance myself from my trauma. that said, it's too fucking infuriating to see people i've known for years attack or belittle a woman who is facing one of the worst experiences of her life all to prevent a bad man from gaining power that he does not deserve.  so here it is:
#whyididntreport 
because i agreed to go to the party, and i knew that others would assume that meant i agreed to be subsequently assaulted by multiple people. my own close blood relative told me it was my fault due to my actions. if my own family didn't have my back when i told them what happened, i had zero hope for cops and prosecutors and friends to have my back. i also didn't report because i didn't want my friends to have to be witnesses against their other friends, my attackers, even though i never owed them that courtesy. yeah, it's complicated, and yeah i let the pieces of shit live free lives and maybe do the same thing to other girls...i'm not proud of it but i am not about to let anyone blame me for it. reporting is ugly and hard and i chose to avoid that path.
#ifuckingbelieveher #doctorford #drford #christineblaseyford stand strong, i believe you. thank you for doing this. ♡

text:
resharing from my facebook. because i know some people out there need an ally. 
my friend posted this- what i’ve been feeling. 
i need to know these things- so that i can protect both my girls and both my boys. they need people who are going to be safe havens, who don’t question their truths, who will love them, who will set the example of how to act and behave. who will be allies and crusaders. who will stand up for what’s right. 
as a mental health professional- i’ve seen and been exposed to more than the average. this entire #metoo movement touches me both as a professional, for all the men and women who’ve cried in my office and dared to share their truths with me- and also hits me personally. 
friends and family, take care of yourselves. if you need an ally who will believe you, someone who’ll listen to your truth and your story, feel free to reach out to me. i’ll be here for you. #mydoorisalwaysopen

none of my abusers ever suffered a single consequence. .tw

i  am pissed off at the world. my wounds are from childhood. my abuser whittled my self esteem to nothing so i'd never speak out about the abuse i received in lieu of love and protection. he took my self worth and made me believe i deserved every piece of shit that came my way. .
.
i don't know how old i was when i lost my sense of self worth but it developed into complex ptsd and as an adult my life is fucking hard and miserable because of nothing i did or could have done to protect myself. .
.
i developed a complex of fighting for justice in the face of injustice. because they never paid. i never received justice. this cycle repeated itself until i was wise enough to stop it. .
.
then this bullshit piece of shit trash pile walks into the world and people who are supposed to protect people like me looked the other way and now our rights are flying out the window. .
.
.
our president and the party who brought him to power whittled our country's self esteem and self worth down to nothing and now they are gonna rape the shit out of us.
.
.
prove me fucking wrong. .
.
i beg you to.
.
.

text:

.
i’m not sure when the film will be out in full, but i’ll keep everyone posted. thank you for checking out this trailer in the meantime! .
.

text:
i am exhausted. emotionally, mentally, and physically. i am exhausted as a woman, a mother, a wife, a daughter, a friend, a survivor, but most importantly a human being witnessing all of..this. i have watched dr. ford be braver than i ever was. to this day i have never told my family what happened to me. i was and am too ashamed, afraid of being judged and labeled yet another cautionary tale of a 17 year old girl who went to a party and lost control of her situation. i watched her testimony weeping, biting my nails to the quick, feeling her pain, in awe of her courage. also completely baffled that at the same moment my daughter blissfully napped innocent and unaware as this amazing human stood up for her, for all of us, fighting the monsters that hide in plain sight. my heart has broken and come together countless times for all the survivors out there who have come forward to speak their truth, to be heard, to heal, and move forward united. my deepest gratitude, love, and light goes to you, to us. i believe you. i believe dr. ford. i believe me.
.
i refuse to give up and will continue to love this bat-shit crazy world. i will continue to fight the war on hate, but most importantly i will continue to fight for joy and love....that’s why we are all fucking here, amiright?!?! .
.
“‘may our daughters grow up without her trauma but with her strength.’ may our sons grow up to be allies, co-creating a world that celebrates women’s courage and equality.” .

text:
trigger warning:

i can’t even count on one hand how many men have asked my permission to kiss me.
i wonder how many men know how much of a big deal that is.
in fact, id need an extra hand or two to count how many times i’ve had to jerk my hand away from men in clubs + in bars who think that grabbing me 
is a way to get my attention.
i wonder how many know how much anxiety that creates.
i wonder how many even care..
i believe that it’s hard for women to love safely. 
i believe it’s hard for men to know how to love women safely.
i believe it’s hard for humans to realize how important safety is in relationships.
hard, but not impossible.
_____________________________________________________
i posted in my ig story on the day of the blasey-ford vs. kavanaugh story saying, “it’s sad to see how many of us can say #metoo.” because it is.
hearing stories of my sisters being harassed + my friends being assaulted.
for my brother to hear stories of such. + to have to force myself to ignore shit like cat calling + hypersexuality on the daily. .. this is why it’s hard for us.
it’s hard for us to even open up about it.
because it happens too often. 
because we were taught that it happens so often that we normalize it.
because we were taught that it’s not a big deal.
too many of our stories are pierced pain + it’s never voiced. 
it’s pain that never goes away.
_____________________________________________________
i don’t even get into politics. but this is a human rights issue. this is a women’s rights issue. this is one of the many reasons why it’s hard for women to love safely.
i thank god that i’ve never experienced her exact experience, but nevertheless.. i can understand an ounce of how she feels.
i’ve shed tears by knowing that i can understand only an ounce of how she feels.
i can understand an ounce of how all women feel.
voiceless. powerless. hopeless.
+ how? when we were created to be the exact opposite.. _____________________________________________________
thank you god for the air to breathe, but still. this issue is suffocating us. #ibelieveher

text:
if i could give advice to the high school me, i would have told her to be as brave as this woman... to speak up and turn that trauma into something positive... i would tell her it wasn’t her fault... i’d tell her not to bury it so deep in the ground - it would only become an endless self-worth conversation to which she would always lose.
.
i would remind her that this didn’t happen to her - that it happened for her so she can guide other survivors to their highest self worth ....and forgiveness ...and strength ....and fierce self love. .
.
the longest distance is the journey from your head to your heart.  your heart will love you even when your mind speaks into shame and guilt and hurt and loneliness... take that journey - operate out of your heart despite the tumultuous terrains... your voice matters and can be a vehicle of healing.
.
this woman took the courage, not just to speak out but to speak inward - which was the tougher battle.... no matter how long ago that traumatic moment happened, it’s never too late to turn your trauma into a movement of strength and empowerment.
.
this is my life, my journey - and i’m in tandem with hers.
.
the very thing that cut my soul in half is now the electricity that lights my bright and loving heart. .
.

text:
got asked today why i put that i’m a survivor on my sign (i’ve never admitted it in public before), but yesterday during dr. ford’s hearing, calls to the national sexual assault hotline spiked 147% — so for me the answer to that is that we have the potential to listen, heal, and grow when we use our voices and share our truths, even though it is often painful to do so. 
we use our voices because we are stronger than if we don’t. we use our voices with the hope that even just one mind will change, that even just one woman years from now will be safer, that even just one less person will be scared to live their life freely. 
it never gets easier to talk about this but when all of us come together, there’s a possibility it will get better. i choose to believe it will. 
everyone else today, just by showing up, believes the same. not only that, but they are prepared to use their voices through the power and privilege of voting. only 2 people weren’t registered but by the end of the protest (and with the help of this shirt), even they were set too.
justice will prevail, even if it takes far longer than it should. i refuse to believe anything else.

text:
holding my sisters close, and sending love and appreciation to the conscious men in my life. the fact that this is still an issue is painful. the fact that it resonates so deeply with so many is painful. the fact that change seems so slow is painful. everything hurts and it is so difficult to keep doing the work. but alas, we must go on. the world cannot survive without us. it is dark times like these that call for our light. ✨
.
.
.
my words fail me right now; everything seems so...corrupted. but i promised myself i would write every day, so...a poem for you. #inmyfeelings #empath #collective #consciousness

blessed bloodright:

the #blood that runs
between my thighs -
a river of death and rebirth -
starting the cycle again
from the beginning.

every drip, a memory. 
every drop, a reason.

reminding me 
of the first time
of every time
of my goddess power
despite my assault(s)

it calls to me,
saying:
"woman -
you are everything.
you are life itself. "

i want to bathe
in my own blood.
i want to give life
to the images in my mind.
dip my fingers
into my own ink pot
and paint
a new reality.

expression.
decompression.

the human in me
wants to eat the flesh
of the men who have wronged me.
i want to feel the fire
that burns them
in the special hell
for cowards.
i want to taste
the sweet aroma in the air
of revenge.

but i am a godly woman,
a goddess woman
and i do not sink
to allow another to swim.
i raise my head
and i inhale deeply,
sending love
and bittersweet forgiveness
and i keep walking
talking
acting
coping
bleeding

doing the work
that the white man
gets all the credit for
even though he takes his cut
without asking
and with no consequence
for the ultimate crimes
he commits

soon, the flood will come
the blood of the survivors
will rain down upon you
and you will no longer 
be able to run,
little boy.

we see you.
we are not fooled by you.
the quiet whisperings of truth
are becoming so loud
i can taste them.
the ones that are weak
and easily tempted
will not be able to hide
anymore.

we are fierce
and we are coming for you.
this bloodshed
will not be for nothing.
.
.
#webelieveyou
#believesurvivors
#tellyourstory
#metoo
#rapeculture
#riseup

text:
re-ordered this brilliant work by toni morrison. it’s time to read it again in this moment of great trigger.  mz. morrison helps me make sense of it all. 
anytime the violation of a human is this common place, it should be treated as a human rights issue. after all, it is the right to safety, dignity, and autonomy of ones own body that is being violated. physically, mentally, emotionally, and spiritually.

@jonathansingletary song don’t fight alone is my companion for the nights artistic peace. to all the survivors who done been through something no matter the scale. this song is from me to you. {on the road to touch the sky it ain’t no easy way
i just hope you put some faith in me 
cause you don’t have to fight alone 
no you don’t have to fight alone 
no you don’t have to fight all on your own} 
#metoo, #believeher, #anitahill, #drchristineblaseyford, #listentowomen , #believewomen, #istillbelieveanitahill

text:
there’s this moment before the day gives into slumber. when it stretches its long limbs and shrugs off the work of the day. when birds are still flying home to roost and bats have already begun their frantic flight above the calm steady seas. this moment beyond the glory of the red, gold, bronze painted sky and before the blackness that is to come. my heart settles from anticipation to stillness. from pretense to grace. no more illusion of what i must be. or what i must do to fit excellence between the hours of 9-5. my face rests. my soul rests. i feel at home here in the in between. in the in between pages of my life. not anticipating. not waiting. just being. just me .
.
.
.

it is time for a change...
standing up for ourselves is not a crime...

text:
victims are only #victims in the minds of those who so easily judge or walk all over them. those who have walked in similar shoes see more than just scars and what’s behind the smiles and/or tears. they #believethem not because of whether a situation is true or not. they believe them because when they look at them they recognize the face of a fierce #warrior whose daily #smallsteps are a giant leap for self and in result, humankind.💥💪🏼👩🏼💪🏼
.

.

.
just something i’ve been considering today. #somethingtothinkabout
.
.

text_retweet:
#repost @mattmcgorry 
brett kavanaugh is the symptom. rape culture and patriarchy is the disease. same with trump. same with the rapists outted by the #metoo movement (not to mention white supremacy, capitalism, etc). men, if you actually care...listen to women, and the women on the front lines of the anti-sexist, anti-rape culture, feminist movement and get to work. and if you’re a man, wondering if i’m talking about you, i can assure you that i am. you need to be a man that other men know stands against rape culture. that other men know won’t let this shit slide. that other men can come to you with their questions about what to do to be a part of the solution. we all have circles of influence, and we need to influence them. we don’t deserve credit for not being a kavanaugh, a trump, or a weinstein. the only way to change this world to make it safer for women and girls is to be preemptive and do the shit that you see almost no other men doing. when you see lots of women in your life re-posting an article or a meme about rape culture, but not men doing it, you do it. violence against women is *men’s* violence against women over 99% of the time. this is our job to fix. guys, next time you hear liberal men complaining about kavanaugh, ask “what are you doing to end rape culture?”

the heart is messy.  feelings are messy … they’re not meant to be neat and packaged in perfection. *

our hearts don’t work in the ways of pie charts and reading lists ... they don’t operate in the time and space continuum that our minds operate in.  how often has our heart revisited memories as if they were current events? *

our hearts are messy and beautiful and colorful … we have so much to learn from them … *

but how often do we shut our hearts down, react out of fear, stay within the comfort of our patterns, try to cram them into a perfectly packaged sentence or post or gesture? *

if we express our heart authentically … do you think it’s going to be neat? packaged perfectly?

this is life.

and it’s messy. *
*
*
*
*
*

text:
who’s to blame|i was 5 years old, surrounded by a loving family who loved god and loved people. i can still remember the dress that my mom dressed me in on that sunday morning. it was a yellow dress with frills and ruffles. my hair done in perfect braids adorned with yellow barrettes. on this particular sunday, at the beginning of the church service, i had to go to the bathroom. 
i made my way down the stairs to the bathroom, upon exiting i found myself being abruptly picked up and pushed up against the wall. confused & disoriented, i finally realized that i was being held by a young man that apparently followed me and waited for me. he proceeded to pull my dress up. i remember the lace that was sown around the trim of my dress. he placed his hand in my panties and began to touch me. i was left feeling scared & confused. he continued to molest me for some time after that day which started to seem like it was a regular part of life. during that time i kept what was happening a secret as i was afraid i would be judged. soon came more young men that began to molest me. i started to think that there was a stamp on my forehead that said: “touch her.” i was molested until the age of 11 years old. the years that followed, i carried the guilt of that pain. i didn’t love who i saw in the mirror, and i blamed myself for what happened to me. i started to have low self-esteem, i cried a lot, and i believed i wasn’t good enough. now that i am an adult, whose to blame for what happened to me??? for years i blamed myself and believed i was the cause of the trauma that happened to me. but why do we do this to ourselves. why do we blame the victim. why do we then point fingers at them for not telling what happened to them until years later. why do we shame them? why do we point fingers? so i ask whose to blame, the 5 year old in this photo or....... @metoomvmt @timesupnow #survivor #notavictim of #sexualabuse #beyondthebarriers of #depression there is #hope #selflove #selfcare #melaningirlmovement #hopestillstands @essence  @redtabletalk #metoo #timesup #bmore #dc #dmv #baltimore excerpt @audible_com by injoy magazine

text:
to survivors,

sending love to all the survivors and gratitude for those who are holding space - as survivors as well. yesterday was hard as hell.
.
this nation continues to remind us of its foundation and commitment to white supremacist misogyny - especially through its courts, agents, and leader.
.
so many of us are working hard to survive its legacy and ongoing assaults - physically, symbolically, spiritually, emotionally, and intellectually.
.
to us - as we rise - in resistance, in revolution, in peace. however you come - i honor survivors. all damn day.
.
so let today do nothing to deter us but to further the fervor - whatever the outcome.
.
we were born and raised through the fire. we've been through the fire. so we know - we are built to last and aren't going anywhere.
.
with love, 
aapi women lead
.
#survivornarratives #survivorloveletter #whyididntreport #metoo #aapiwomenlead #aapi #api #westandwithyou #believesurvivors

text:
#thepatriarchyisover × pluto stations direct in capricorn × -
-

the biggest saying in astrology is "as above so below." when shit is going down politically/socially eye always look at the planetary weather and everyyyy time there's forces up there that *directly* coincide with the social issues hitting our world atm. women/womxn/womban are fed up. we are done holding in our traumas from the patriarchy. past cases of sexual assault are coming to the surface amidst the brett kavanaugh case and we. are just. so. fucking. tired. of. the patriarchy. -
-

enter pluto. pluto is stationing direct on september 30. it has been retrograde since april 22 of this year. naturally pluto rules the underworld, the dead, lies, addictions, hidden agendas, secrets, all that yummy stuff🌈 it rules scorpio. there has been a massive triggering amongst the female collective dealing with both old + new trauma. on a global scale. since april, lies, secrets, addictions have gone rampant as the planet of deceit went backwards in orbit. -
-
as pluto is stationing direct again, guess what that means: secrets are being revealed. if you have been in a place in the past 5 months where no one believes your story, or the perpetrator was never punished, trust that the dark, messy truth is being revealed right now. it is not pretty. it is not easy. it is not quick. it is ugly. it is tiring. but damn does it feel good to speak up. -
-

this is what my guides told me to share with the collective tonite. may you know your truth. continue to speak your truth. know your worth and the universe will provide you what you believe you deserve. take care of your body + mind + soul. please :) one love✨🙏 _________________________________

text: to all those survivors of rape and sexual assault, i know it hurts. i understand that some days you feel like you'll never get out of that horrible moment when someone made you feel unsafe in your own body, in your own existence. and it does get better. and it gets worse. i know that for many of you the news has turned into a repeat of your nightmare. that people you cared for, you trusted, are calling a fellow survivor a dirty whore, a liar, and many bad things. but there are people who believe her, believe you. i believe you. i was raped when i was 14 years old by someone i trusted, someone i called my friend. 10 years later and i still sometimes feel like i'm back in that field, stuck inside a hell that never ends. but i'm not in that field anymore. and you are not back in your hell. you are here, you survived and you are safe with me. in these depressing days, please remember that i and many of your fellow survivors believe you and stand with you. to those who are not survivors, please be kind. please be compassionate and know that every joke you make disparaging a survivor, whether you believe them or not, hurts someone you know, maybe even care for. though the news is making many of us cry and shake, please remember that there is kindness and love in the world. i love you. #metoo #ibelieveher #ibelievechristineblaseyford #rapevictim #victimsofsexualabuse #kindness #love #loveyourself #ibelieveyou #estiwitch

text:
october is approaching! for those who don’t know, october is domestic violence awareness month! 💜

i have decided to publicly share a piece of my story. not for your attention, not for your pity. but to raise awareness...because it happened to #metoo. 
the last few months have been some of the most difficult of my life. i found myself in an abusive relationship earlier this year. verbal and emotional at first...until one day i was assaulted. my bruises have since healed...but that was the easy part. my daily struggles with anxiety and depression have been exacerbated. lately there are more good days than bad, but some days i feel like an open wound exposed to the world. 7 months later and i’m just scratching the surface...healing is hard. it takes time and a lot of effort and most certainly doesn’t happen overnight. if you have a loved one going through something similar...please try to be patient.

patience is something we can all strive for...myself included. i’m currently waiting for a trial date to be set where my abuser is being charged with aggravated assault. this has been a long, drawn out process and i’m ready for it to be over with... but here i wait. 🤷🏻‍♀️ although this experience has been hurtful and traumatic... i wouldn’t trade it for the world. i’m thankful my story is my story. i’m thankful and blessed that i’m here to tell it. 
it’s not just strangers and people on the news...domestic violence doesn’t discriminate. it’s your friends and family, fellow churchgoers, classmates, coworkers. there’s a stigma around domestic violence that silences it’s victims. if someone reaches out...listen. believe them! 
#believesurvivors #metoo #domesticviolenceawarenessmonth #dontcallitacomeback

text:
this week has been rough...and i have to be super real and transparent right now.
*trigger warning* first the full body/ cannot move flu hit me like a ton of bricks. then the kiddo got sick  too, of course. exhausted, sweaty, miserable and emotional it is also the anniversary of my fathers passing in 2012.  and we are coming up on the month i had my miscarriage in in 2011. and the things happening to my friends, family and human family in general...just make me so damn sad. i know i am not perfect, i struggle with depression, anxiety, memories of things from the past haunt me.. i am in a funk. and it makes it hard to stay on track with goals, projects and to not snap at the ones i love the most. what are some of your personal ways of dealing with being in a funk?? #emotional#miscarriage#mentalhealth#rapeawareness#metoo#whyididntreport#deppression#anxiety#losingaparent#innerpeace#innerdemons
