text: why not believe her? she received countless death threats for testifying for one. yet brett kavanaugh is on his way to be confirmed to the supreme court. this is not the time to stay silent because decisions and reactions made now will impact how issues of sexual assault are handled, accepted, given credibility and weight in the future. the debate propelled by the remarkably brave actions of christine blasey ford has the potential to inspire change. it raises questions which can increase awareness of faults in the justice system with regards to the protection of bodily rights and of general misconceptions about women’s motives and credibility. arguments against show an emotional disconnection from the personal consequences of rape in victim blaming and perpetrator protection, but also hypocrisy regarding why a woman chooses to take the stand and testify about her rape (and how difficult that actually is). #christineblaseyford #believeher #believeherstory #staystrong #unitedstates #supremecourt #trumpadministration #consent #womenempowerment #womensrights #feminism #intersectionalfeminism #awereness  #metoo

text:
when i was 16 years old, a man in his late 30’s in a position of power, started a conversation when we were alone in his office about what he thought it would be like to have sex with me.  he then grabbed my face and kissed me on the lips and tried to stick his tongue in my mouth...he laughed when i ran out of the room.

why am i telling you this?  because you didn’t know.  i didn’t put #metoo as my status, i didn’t consider myself to be violently assaulted, but the behavior was predatory, and gross, and crossed a huge moral line.

what would i do if i saw him in a position of higher power?  if i saw him working with children?  if i saw him somewhere that i thought he could prey on a young person and perhaps take it further?

would i tell?  would i risk the shame that could come with it?  would my kids read bull 💩 on facebook about how i was a liar?  how i was looking for attention?  would my dating habits or how i dressed come into play?

i’m not telling you this to garner sympathy or be woe is me because i’m so shattered, it’s not something that haunts me, but i guarantee you there is someone on your friends list that is haunted....who sees the absolute trash you post about women who claim to be assaulted that you don’t believe, that you ridicule and make fun of.

think about that friends, let it sink in.  it could be someone you love, someone you care deeply for, and your digging a dagger right into them.

be better.

#believesurvivors #stopbeingassholes

text_retweet:
what’s happening in the us is happening to us all. we are one.  #repost @lindsaymaxfield with @get_repost
・・・
as we witness history being made, we must never forget the women who have gone before...
.
we inherit you. your skin, your eyes, the way you looked at the world. the way the world looked at you.
.

we inherit your fear of touch. your fear of being struck down. your fear of being found out. of being caught.
.

we too know this fear. it is ours and it is yours. we know the danger that awaits a woman who is owned, and even a woman who is owned by no one.
.

we know our realness and rawness terrify you, our mothers and grandmothers and so many more. because the world you lived in punished you thoroughly for stepping outside the lines. your soul bears the scars to this day, but the fear never heals over. it rises again with each new danger we face.
.
even our ancient sisters long gone rise with this fear and rush to our side. they protect us and hold us and lift us up ... and yet they also tremble and shake with the rising of this fear. it reminds them of the soul wounds that cry out still to be seen and known and healed and freed.
.

and this is how we heal each other. mothers and sisters and all of us together, spirit and flesh, soul to soul, hand in hand we rise. and we rise. and we rise. and we rise. together we rise until every last one is free.
.
thank you @sdjun_creatives for the art.
.
.
.

.

we too know this fear. it is ours and it is yours. we know the danger that awaits a woman who is owned, and even a woman who is owned by no one.
.

we know our realness and rawness terrify you, our mothers and grandmothers and so many more. because the world you lived in punished you thoroughly for stepping outside the lines. your soul bears the scars to this day, but the fear never heals over. it rises again with each new danger we face.
.
even our ancient sisters long gone rise with this fear and rush to our side. they protect us and hold us and lift us up ... and yet they also tremble and shake with the rising of this fear. it reminds them of the soul wounds that cry out still to be seen and known and healed and freed.
.

and this is how we heal each other. mothers and sisters and all of us together, spirit and flesh, soul to soul, hand in hand we rise. and we rise. and we rise. and we rise. together we rise until every last one is free.
.
thank you @sdjun_creatives for the art.
.
.
.

text:
with the massive wave of testimonies of sexual harassment of women coming into public light lately, we know how disturbing merely listening to the stories of the survivors is. they are triggering, to say the least. the global menace of sexual harassment is pushing us to sadly believe that we are living in a handmaid's tale. in these times, it is a personal request to all the women specifically to come together, to believe each other, to believe the survivors. patriarchy has made us live a lie that women can never be best friends or that they always try and put each other down. let us please break this and restore sisterhood back again. let us be there for our breakdowns. let us not be friends with abusers of other women. let us call them out. and to repeat, let us please believe the survivors. 
artwork by @obrazkovani

text:
this grainy old picture of me was taken around age 13 or 14, just a year or two after my first, ongoing sexual abuse. he was my first boyfriend, older than me, and i was twelve. my first kiss. when i was older and stronger i tried to report it and a police office told me to come back another time because "it's the wrong day to make a report like that." i never went back. but i did start some life altering very self destructive behaviors. 
the second assault came later at age 18. when a good friend of mine orally assaulted me. i did nothing, confused because i had given consent and didn't know i could not take it away. 
neither of these men are likely even aware they did anything wrong.

for years this resulted in dangerous behavior on my part, depression, anxiety, and has affected every relationship i have had. i used to have to disassociate in order to get through sex. young men who knew nothing of what they were doing _ruined_ sex for me with their carelessness. 
#yesallwomen #metoo #ibelievechristineblaseyford #ibelieveher #ibelievewomen #rapeculture

text:
following with interest and empathy the dialogue that has been opened by actress #tanushreedutta in india. it’s no secret that women are sized up and cut down in the hindi film industry and while things are changing, we need more voices to come forward, in sane and clear sighted discussion 🙏
now when i discuss with friends the #metoo movement, the kavanaugh case and closer to home, the voices raised when an actress accuses a reputed hindi film actor of harassment, i look at my daughters, sufi and soleil, and think, how would i want them to be treated? what sort of principles do they need to abide by in the world as they grow? and will they inherit a world that abides by them?
#mysouffle #believesurvivors #changetheculture #daughterlove #futureisfemalebabies #metoo

text:
just venting here. i know there are amazing men out there doing incredible work to help cats, and all animals. but from my experience the majority of rescuers, fosters, tnr folks are women. this is fine (i am so grateful and inspired by you! 🙌). but to be honest i’m sick and l tired of being treated with disrespect by men who do not take me seriously, a lot of which i believe stems from me being a small female, who looks young (younger than i am) and speaks with a generally calm and quiet tone. that is no excuse for disgusting or dismissive behavior. i’ve had enough. you do not know the limits of my strength and determination. thank you to the guys who respect and do not degrade women — though i wish we lived in a world where that doesn’t need to be said. (this post inspired by the current news, yet it’s been festering for a long, long time.) #toxicmasculinity #metoo #feminist #sorrynotsorry #listentowomen #wereinthistogether

text:
💕 reminder 💕

there are so many stories on my feed of women sharing why they didn’t report their sexual assaults and speaking up and i want to take this time to honour each of you for your courage and strength. no matter the severity it’s important and i believe you. 
i didn’t report because i was coerced and therefore believed it was consensual. it wasn’t a no but it wasn’t a yes either. it wasn’t until i read about this as lack of consent that i even considered it a thing. i was also groped by a coworker in a bar. he has a daughter and had asked me to be a mentor to her because he respected me. i saw him at my yoga studio and froze in fear. i almost stopped going. i didn’t report it because he was drunk, i slapped him when it happened and it was ‘just groping’. it was assault. it’s not ok. this has to stop. •
•
•
•
•
•
•
•
#metoo #whyididntreport #ibelieveher #youareloved #reminder #love #selflove #speakup #consent #counsellor #yvr

text:
(2/2) john mccain passed away last august, and took with him the honor, class and integrity of his party. the confirmation of kavanaugh as a justice of the supreme court will take place soon, given how rush the republicans have been in the last few weeks. bill nelson, joe donelly, claire mccaskill, jon tester, doug jones, 6 of the 8 democrat senator in red states or up for tough elections have opposed the nomination. now only senator heidi heitkamp of north dakota, senator joe manchin of west virginia, along with republican senators lisa murkowski of alaska and susan collins of maine can decide the fate of the vacant seat for one of the most powerful positions in the us. the country ranked 10th as the most dangerous countries to be women, and the shameful hearings and treatment of dr. ford as well as other allegations were watched by millions of people all around the world. american women is fighting their best for their benefits and for the future of their daughters. may their battle lead to changes. may their efforts won't be dismissed and ignored. may the victory be with them.

and even though we've come a long way with the momentum of #metoo and #timesup 
it's still hard work being female. 
a dispiriting amount of data released with international women's day (iwd) shows we have a long way to go before we reach equality. 
217 years to be precise!

while we do have female pilots and prime ministers and lot more choice and freedom than the women who came before us, women are still not paid equally to male counterparts, are not present in equal numbers in business or politics, and globally women's education, health and the violence against them is worse than that of men.

iwd is an important opportunity for the wider community to celebrate contributions and gains while also recognising the persistent gender inequality that exists in all countries and contexts.

the battle for equality requires daily effort and attention, not just annual recognition.

gloria steinem, world-renowned feminist, journalist and activist once explained "the story of women's struggle for equality belongs to no single feminist nor to any one organisation but to the collective efforts of all who care about human rights." 🙆‍♀️ .
women's rights are human rights. making the world better for women makes the world better for everybody, period. 🌻

if you haven't already done it - do me a favour? 😍
remind a woman you know that they're talented, essential and deserve the best from the world. .

do your bit to ensure that the future for girls is bright, equal, safe and rewarding. 💕 happy international women's day 💕 .
.
.
. .
.
.

text:
when women like christine blasey ford come forward, and tell their truths—listen. empathize. and when the women in your life feel hurt, belittled, and shut-down—listen. don’t get defensive, this isn’t a competition. most of us have had bosses, ex-boyfriends, family, etc. that have attempted to put us in our place, leading some of us to believe we could never be as smart, strong, resourceful, or successful as a man. and some of us are still recovering from those assholes.
.
i think there is a level of sexism towards women from even the most compassionate men. i’m not calling all men assholes. i’m just saying that we have been taught that men should be one way, and women should be another. and as we’ve mindlessly created those ideas of gender in our head, we’ve picked up habits and behavioral norms that happen to belittle and oppress women. even the most well-intended men, who we can find marching beside us, generally still have programmed notions of how women should be, look, and/or behave.
.
i don’t hate men. as a mom of two boys, i empathize with men. i think men have their own struggles, including not always being able to comfortably express emotions and sensitives. and for that, i’m regularly encouraging the men in my life to express themselves.
.
it’s not like we can just change our preconceived judgements overnight. i understand that. especially under a president who doesn’t hold those values, doesn’t see women as equal counterparts, and who continues to spread animosity which is only dividing us. dividing the sexes. the races. the classes. but i’m still hopeful, that as humans, we can be mindful of our prejudices, and actively try to remove them.
.
.
.
#ibelieveher #ibelievechristineblaseyford #timesup #metoo #womensmarch #womensmovement #flexyourfemale #bossbabe #graphicdesigner #womenwhodesign

text:
📖
•••
🇫🇷 coucou,
autre extrait de ma nouvelle qui se trouvera dans le recueil #desauteursautoeditessemobilisentcontreleharcelementderue 💪
en tout, 17 nouvelles et donc 17 voix pour s’exprimer sur le harcèlement dans les lieux publics envers des femmes, des couples homosexuels, des victimes du racisme, etc.
des genres et des tons différents. certaines réussissent à nous faire sourire, d’autres nous donnent envie de distribuer des 👊
la version 📚 fera environ 350 pages 😊
bonne journée ☀️
•••
📒 vous pouvez retrouver mes livres, les ajouter à votre pal et consulter des extraits sur les sites de lecture comme babelio, livraddict, booknode et goodreads à mon nom d’autrice s. n. lemoing 😊
🛍 ils sont disponibles gratuitement en emprunt avec amazon kindle ou à 2.99€ pour les romans et 0.99€ pour les épisodes de lescalicesdutemps au format ebook, et entre 8 et 11€ pour les versions papier 📖
•••
🇬🇧 hi,
this is an excerpt of my novella for a short story collection about street harassment 💪
basically, it says:
‘i hold on to my memories, to my life, to me. to all the things they try to take from us, or erase. as if we were only here to please them.’
there’s a facebook page for the book. 17 novellas have been selected, 17 voices for women, queer people, people of color, etc. who have been harassed.
have a great time ☀️
•••
📚 if you love medieval fantasy & badass female characters you can read more info about my novel 'powerful: the realm of harcilor'. it's been acclaimed by 90+ french literary bloggers & nearly a dozen of english speaking book lovers 😊
link in bio.
🛍 my novel is available for free for kindle unlimited subscribers, as an ebook at 1,15$ or 0,99£, etc. & paperback for $14 👍

text:
@brennatwohy 
i'm sitting here tonight,  thinking about what's happening in our society,  and about the ripples of the kavanaugh confirmation hearings and the power of of dr. christine blasey ford's testimony.  of the gratitude and relief that women collectively felt to have our wounds spoken with such power,  grace and dignity and the despair of that testimony being pearls cast before swine. i've been thinking about the women coming into my treatment room raging and hurting,  and i've been thinking about my own. ⭐it's an amazing time to be alive. it's an amazing time to be a sister,  a healer,  a sacred witness,  a blessing giver. i've done a lot of work in my own shadows so that i can hold space for them. i keep thinking about all the women sharing their stories of why they didn't tell. ⭐ i'm thinking about the consequences of having actually told,  before i could understand that the fabric of society was woven with women's silence. i think about how,  because i was so young,  it was my mother's and my grandmother's characters that were maligned and assassinated because they protected me.  how it divided my family,  how we had to leave the church community my family had belonged to for 30 years. i keep thinking about the family member who sided with my abuser when the abuse became public knowledge,  and how he sought me out at both my grandparents funerals to say how unfortunate that all was and what a good man my abuser was. never asking what i thought. it took until the second funeral before i could trust myself to tell the truth with dignity. to not question myself or my worth. to not need to matter to this man. ⭐ i'm thinking about how powerful it is to be at peace. to be at peace with the fact that it happened,  that it has impacted every facet of my life, and that i'm not playing the victim to say so. to know the difference between making peace and being at peace. the tides of time are changing and the reign of these men will come to an end. it's a long game,  but i truly believe that it will happen because power moves as a pendulum.  blessing and holding the sisterhood tonight. #metoo #stopkavanaugh #believesurvivors #whyididntreport
name: Heather Reuble, LMT

text:

5sos: talk about mental illness and do music about it, criticize capitalism and society as well as toxic relationships

twenty one pilots: don't even get me started. great personalities with deep meaningful lyrics and damn good music; still humor and always positive on hinting on staying alive

got7: give up half of their clothing when it rains and protect their fans from the rain; do random 'stages' on the street when they meet fans, perform at hospitals for free, support women on #metoo 
fall out boy: own fund for over 20,000 children for education, food & more

b.a.p : criticize war, education systems, politics and their own agency, unicef ambassadors since they're 16-20 yrs old 
fewjar: do 24hrs+ live streams and donate for sth new every year

bts: talk about literally every issue they can find like beauty standards, racism in the government & police,  education, capitalism etc etc, collab with unicef, mental illness discussions & self love appreciation af.

stray kids: literally say fuck it, attend ny pride privately all together (yes, all nine), discuss topics as bullying, homesickness, mental illness and healing process, fight any kind of beauty- and gender standards 
simple plan: do mvs with their fans, a lot of them being about succeeding over depression, a song about how music can save lifes

exo: openly support homosexuality, feminism and gender neutrality, help out at children's hospitals and donate, fuck gender expectations in any kinda way 
linkin park: a lot of mental illness discussion and donations & suicide preventions 
imagine dragons: promote love, peace and kindness, positivity and self love

monsta x: pro-black, learn languages of every country they have a concert in, step out of their limousine with flowers for their waiting fans, playing gay roles in their own music videos

one direction: songs about toxic relationships, #rainbowdirection, songs for the fans, hs totally supporting women & lgbtq, unicef collabs”

text: yesterday i recieved an email containing the link to a blog post written by a british midwife. i read her words and felt a sinking sensation in the pit of my tummy... the link is in the btsf bio... also more in my stories... she speaks of the state of midwifery in the nhs, the devastating effect it has on midwives and their patients. she highlights the whelm report and says that senior midwifery professionals are told not to share it, to keep it from midwives in case it puts them off being midwives at all. this is all 💔 women, both birthing mothers and birthing professionals deserve decent care and humane conditions to work and birth in. this the uk in the 21st century. it is not ok. tbh the government should be utterly ashamed and held to account. i'd love to hear your thoughts on this... @birthbetter @mother_of_daughters @lucianaberger @gabyhinsliff @evawiseman @guardian @nhsvoices @theobgynmum @nhsenglandldn @rebecca.schiller @drrebeccamoore @mumologist #birthtrauma #midwifery #nhs #whelmreport #metoo #notok #ukhealth
name: Birth Trauma Support Family

text:
sums it up right now. 
like many abuse/assault/rape survivors i felt the sense of the collective holding of breath this week. spanning way past a us issue, way past a senate issue this transcended borders and ages and everything. 
sending love to all the women (and men) who are hurting like hell right now.

the tide is turning

there is a new dawn 
the patriarchy is crumbling and this is their last snatch at power 
we will regroup stronger and louder and more united because of what is happening

your voice is needed. your story is important. 
i believe you. 
i am unplugging this weekend and getting outside. spending time with my wee lad. 
rephrase self care to essential me time maintenance.

it’s not indulgent it’s necessary. 
if you are joining us for the online sisterhood festival starting monday i’ll be sharing the line up on sunday night 
sending big love

ps if you need to hear an example of the strong, positive masculine have a watch of the clip in the comments. compassionate men are out there ( i live with 2 of them) and amidst everything we need to hear those compassionate men chiming in loud to say no more, times up and we believe women!
#believewomen #drford #timesup #riseofthebadass #metoo

text:
rape is a way to feel powerful; to dominate another human being. and as rapists are 99% above the law, what better way to bury one’s insecurities than to push a girl down and turn the music up so that the world won’t hear her scream? we can do better. we live in a society where we don’t have to beat each other up to be respected. why aren’t we taking advantage of that? why are we still doing this? why do we still seek to polish those in power like they're squeaky clean, while those without it are dragged through the mud for telling the truth? it’s because the truth doesn’t matter to us—54% of republicans think brett kavanaugh should be confirmed even if the allegations are true. boys will, after all, be boys. as long as we believe this stupid lie that men cannot control their sexual impulses and that rape itself is about sex, women will have no freedom. sexual aggression is about shame, insecurity and repression. which means the aggressor is responsible. forty years later, society still can’t believe it. forty years, and why would we come forward? because we're hoping that in another forty years, things will have finally changed. if all we have in this game of he-said-she-said are our testimonies, then we'll keep giving them. #metoo
.
.
.

text:
rund um die #metoo bewegung drehen sich die unterschiedlichsten fragen und perspektiven. wir fragen deshalb: was kann die philosophie der liebe und der sexualität beisteuern, um die auseinandersetzung zwischen befürworter und kritikern der #metoo kampagne besser zu verstehen?

diskutiere mit uns folgende vorschläge:
- freiheit statt zustimmung: warum das einverständnisparadigma mangelhaft ist und was es bedeutet, sich als freie sexuelle subjekte entfalten zu können.
- sozialkritik statt moralische empörung: warum es langfristig wirkungsvoller ist, die sexuelle begegnungen strukturierenden sozialen normen kritisch zu hinterfragen, als individuen moralisch zu beurteilen.

das gespräch mit dr. federica gregoratto geht diesen fragen nach und thematisiert die rolle der experimentellen freiheit.

eintritt 15 franken / ahv/iv 10 franken

reservationen bitte nur unter events@philosophie.ch

text:
it’s 3:14 am. i just finished watching the entirety of dr. christine blasey ford and brett kavanaugh’s testimonies before the us senate. all eight hours of their testimony and questioning.
.
.
.
i told myself that i would watch a recap of the “major moments.” i told myself that i would skip through to the “important parts.” i could not bring myself to look away or miss any part, because as i watched, (even as a canadian) i felt history unfolding before me.
.
.
.
dr. blasey ford - i believe you. unequivocally. emphatically. vehemently. the way she carried herself through such an intensely difficult and traumatic experience with poise, eloquence, and grace was inspiring. the courage and strength she was required to draw upon in order to share her story of sexual assault in such a public and unforgiving manner is unfathomable. dr. blasey ford is the very definition and embodiment of a heroine. she stood, she spoke, for all women. for all survivors. for all of us who have experienced sexual harassment, assault, violence, or rape. if she does not represent you, she represents someone you know. someone you love. someone who 36 years later still bears the burden of a fateful summer afternoon where her body and her being was not respected as her own. where two men “had a laugh” at her expense. .
.
.
and yet. she has persisted. she is accomplished, intelligent, empathetic. she is resourceful. she is resilient. she is a force to be reckoned with. she is history in the making. .
.
.
all survivors’ stories are important. her story is important. my story is important. your story is important. 💛
.
.
.
#believesurvivors #metoo #drchristineblaseyford #christineblaseyford #ibelieveher #istandwithher #ibelieveyou

text: alles ist gut - jetzt im kino!!!! ein beruhigender titel für einen beunruhigenden film: beiläufig und sehr realistisch erzählt regisseurin und drehbuchautorin eva trobisch von einer frau, die nach einer vergewaltigung so tut, als sei nichts passiert. mit beiläufiger leichtigkeit, manchmal sogar witzig, zeigt eva trobisch eine frau, die alles andere als ein opfer ist und sein will. janne geht mit der vergewaltigung um wie mit einem schnupfen: ist nun mal passiert, ist lästig, kann man nix machen. zwei minuten schlechter sex … was soll's? aenne schwarz spielt diese junge frau sehr rotzig, sehr vernünftig und insgesamt unerhört faszinierend in all ihren realistischen facetten, wobei hier und da auch eine gewisse verletzlichkeit deutlich wird. und die zeigt dann endgültig: es geht nicht nur um sexualisierte gewalt. es geht um macht. "alles ist gut" geht jeden an. er heizt die #metoo-debatte nicht an und lässt raum für eigene gedanken und grundlegende fragen, wie man sich respektvoll in der gesellschaft verhält. ☝☝☝ #derfilmtyp #kinotipp #allesistgut #aenneschwarz #andreasdöhler #hanslöw #tilonest #linawendel #lisahagmeister #evatrobisch

#repost with @repostlyapp @mantrasandmiracles holy hell it only took a day for the whole damn thing to fall to pieces. 😮 • 1) it is so important we are talking about this stuff. we have to talk about it. • 2) if the talking moves from creating a space and dialogue that encourages growth, evolution, understanding, compassion, accountability and healing to attack and division, they have won. make no mistake, they want us divided. • 3) it is so important we are talking about this stuff.
watching dr. ford’s testimony reminds me that we move on with our lives, build empires, forge new relationships yet our bodies don’t forget. i could feel the layers of repeated trauma from countless events from my childhood and adolescence reverberate through every cell in my body.
beauties, you may not want to shout from the rooftops but i invite you to talk, shout, speak out in order to release what will continue poison us if we keep silent allowing the feeling of shame and guilt hidden.
we spend so much time apologizing for taking up space in this world!! our leadership is needed more than ever!

text: i want to send love & strength to every girl and woman beset this week by memories of their recent or more distant past and the indignities and assaults they have not talked about, or did not report to ‘authorities’. these things are never forgotten but sometimes are put away, tamped down, carried with us as scars that we are reminded of again and again, by the news, by someone else’s experience, by a comment or sound or a song, or for a reason we can’t identify - just as an object you want to stay submerged can have a mind of its own. we’ve seen how ‘authorities’, some of the men in charge of things, banks of these men setting themselves literally above others, in mahogany rows of desks in committee rooms and their henchpeople will hear our stories and perhaps they’ll say as they did this week - well, you seem credible but we don’t care. even though this has changed you forever and altered the way you see the world, they are saying, and filled you with indelible fear and rage and altered self-image, or made you spikier and angrier and braver, or caused you to forever curtail and trim your life, down to how you speak, what you tell, how you get home and whether you want to go home, we, the some men in charge, do not care enough to be swayed from this other thing, which we care about much more than we care about you or women like you or the girl you were once. nothing you say now will be enough, they say, in angry and impatient voices, insulted by our rage, our politeness, our voices of any kind. i am thinking of us all this week, when a frightened woman’s word raised against a us supreme court nominee is said to be ‘wrong’. a woman who has brought herself no advantage. a woman i believe. i believe in you, too. you don’t owe anyone your story, but you owe yourself care. and kindness. take a breath, take what you need - solitude or time with friends. whatever our different experiences, millions of women and their allies are feeling for each other right now. hug your girls. teach your boys. #metoo #drblaseyford #womenempowerment #forthegirls #takecare photo by wolfgang sievers, 1938, collection of the national library of australia.

text:
if there is one female who has not faced unwanted sexual advances/harrassment or sexual abuse please speak out.
restore my hope in humanity. please.
many of us do not speak of these experiences. we keep them in a deep dark place lest they dim our light.
#enough #metoo #notalone

good people,
we must not enourage this insidious mentality that explains, accepts or excuses violence. violence against women remains one of the most tolerated criminal acts across the globe.
stop femicide.
end sexual abuse & rape.
shame the perpetrator not the victim. 
#enough

text:
tw: sexual assault.

as a survivor the past few days have not been the easiest. i know this is true for many people who are watching and listening. luckily, i have been very busy so it hasn't manifested in the worst of ways for me. i just haven't had the time to really ponder it. but my thoughts are jumbled with flashbacks of my trial. for those who do not know, i was raped by an ex while i was in college. i did everything right and went to the police and the hospital. but at trial he was still found not guilty. he still walks around in the same county i live in with a wife and a child. he has been able to move on with his sad little existence without a care in the world. while it has taken me years to get to the point i am at in my healing. i just want other survivors to know that they are not alone and i care and i believe you. this has been a rough week, but we will persevere.

#believeher #sexualassault #survivor #healing #ptsd #posttraumaticstressdisorder #metoo
